title.narrative: CCE FOR COVID-19 VACCINE DEMAND

description.narrative: Communities have increased knowledge, positive attitude and demand for COVID-19 Vaccine, particularly in target countries, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Caregivers have improved knowledge and skills to adopt recommended health and nutrition care practices, particularly in target countries.

title.narrative: Communities have increased knowledge, positive attitude and demand for COVID-19 Vaccine, particularly in target countries

description.narrative: UNICEF co-led the COVID-19 risk communication and community engagement (RCCE) response in close coordination with partners. The regional RCCE working group supported all 14 PICTs to ensure that the COVID RCCE response, including COVID-19 vaccine demand generation interventions, were effective. An estimated 1.3 million people were reached using mass media, social media, information, education, and communication (IEC) materials, SMS blasts, social mobilization, and interpersonal communication interventions. A range of community-based stakeholders were engaged, including civil society, traditional leaders, religious institutions, youth groups, media, and the private sector. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:02/02/2022
